## Project Overview
The project is an automated testing system for a mobile application, built using Python, Pytest, and Appium. The architecture follows the Page Object Model (POM) principles, ensuring readability, modularity, and easy scalability of the test suite.

The primary goal of the project is to provide a reliable, flexible, and maintainable automation framework that accelerates the release cycle, increases application stability, and helps detect issues early.
The tests reflect real user scenarios, with a strong focus on stability, repeatability, and minimizing code duplication.

The project also includes custom functionality for:

validating and verifying data stored in MongoDB,

comparing backend database values with UI data,

checking data integrity and schema correctness,

automated validation of values, formats, and structures,

simplifying repetitive data-related checks,

executing MongoDB queries to fetch the latest record (via sorting) so the AI can analyze and understand the structure of stored documents.

In addition, the AI agent works primarily in advisory mode.
It provides suggestions, explanations, and guidance, while all implementation and file creation are performed manually by the developer.
The agent generates code, creates files, or modifies project structure only when explicitly requested, ensuring full developer control over the project.

The system is built around the following principles:

Clear separation between test logic and page interaction logic.

Centralized management of waits, utilities, validations, and database operations.

Use of Pytest fixtures for environment setup and database connections.

Strong type hints and documentation for key components.

High-level, readable assertions focused on business outcomes rather than technical details.

The project is designed for long-term scalability and team collaboration: its structure, rules, and architecture allow developers to onboard quickly and extend the test suite effectively.